One Catholic was shot dead and two others wounded  Wednesday when a lone gunman burst into a taxi company office in a Catholic  neighborhood of Armagh, southwest of Belfast, and opened fire, police said.
The victims were not immediately identified and there was no immediate  claim of responsibility for the attack..
On Tuesday, two Catholic workmen were shot dead by Protestant loyalist  gunmen on a Belfast construction site. Those killings were claimed by the  Ulster Volunteer Force.
